Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of eighteen (18) years.   Eleven (11) years initial confinement, followed by seven (7) years extended supervision.  Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Maintain absolute sobriety;
2) AODA asssessment and follow through counseling;
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Maintain full-time employment/job search combination;
5) Have no contact with Kokoya Perry's family without agent's approval;
6) Write a letter of apology to Kokoyo Perry's family and specifically to his mother, George;
7) Pay costs of action;
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
9) Pay restitution of $2,881.00 to George Perry for funeral expenses.  Court orders financial obligations shall be paid at the rate of 25% of the prison wages and work release funds.  The balance remaining at release from prison to be paid as a condition of extended supervision at a rate determined by the supervising agent.
Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Earned Release Program.  
Defendant's DNA is already on file.  
Defendant is given credit for 412 days time already served.  
